PrecisOrder (a) authorizing the Minister of INDIAN AFFAIRS AND NORTHERN DEVELOPMENT to act as FEDERAL INTERLOCUTOR for Métis and Non-status Indians and to enter into Contribution Agreements with organizations representing Métis and off-reserve Aboriginal peoples; and (b) terminating the authorization conferred upon the President of the Queen's Privy Council of Canada by Order in Council P.C. 2003-2092; effective July 20, 2004.
